title: What can I do if my phone can't find any available Wi-Fi network after I turn on Wi-Fi?
answer:
l   Restart the Wi-Fi hotspot device, such as your wireless router.

l   Restart Wi-Fi on your phone.

l   Restart your phone.

l   If the problem persists, make sure MAC address filtering is not enabled on your wireless router. For details about configuration on the router, see the router User Guide.
